GET.desc: GET is the most important query, letting you obtain useful information like ids, data, seafuncs information and more.

UPDATE.desc: UPDATE like it's name suggests, updates a value in a table.

EXISTS.desc: EXISTS checks if a value exists, and if so, it will return true.

DOWNLOAD.desc: DOWNLOAD downloads a file from your database.

DELETE.desc: DELETE removes a level, comment or user from the database

JOIN.desc: JOIN joins two queries to form one, usually related to GET.

RAND.desc: RAND gets a random level, comment or user.

LOGIN.desc: LOGIN and LOGOFF like they suggest, are a login system only when you enable that only mods can use SeaFuncs.
